{"lemma":"جَناحٌ","slug":"جَناحٌ","root":"ج.ن.ح","root_slug":"ج-ن-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-ن-ح","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"جَناح","root":"جنح","pos":"N","occurrence_count":7},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n6451","n6452"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D9%8E%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AD%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wing (organ of flight)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wing (part of army)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wing (part of building)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"shoulder, arm, hand"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"side, edge"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fin"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"projecting roof"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"protection, refuge"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"blame, misdemeanor, transgression, wrong","tags":["singular","singular-only"],"examples":[{"text":"وَلَا جُنَاحَ عَلَيْكُمْ إِن كَانَ بِكُمْ أَذًى مِّن مَّطَرٍ أَوْ كُنْتُم مَّرْضَىٰ أَن تَضَعُوا أَسْلِحَتَكُمْ وَخُذُوا حِذْرَكُمْ","english":"There is no blame upon you if ye are vexed by rain or ye are sick that ye lay down your arms, but exercise caution."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Uncertain; no Semitic cognates exist which are not suspected to be borrowed from Arabic. Likely related to Egyptian ḏnḥ, either through inheritance or through borrowing; also compare جَنَحَ (janaḥa, “to lean”) (both referring to the concept of side).\n\nFrom Middle Persian; compare modern Persian گناه (gonâh)."},"ipa":["/d͡ʒa.naːħ/","/d͡ʒu.naːħ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n6451","headword_ar":"جَنَاحٌ","root":"jnH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yad","text_ar":"يَد"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) [meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wing"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of a bird or flying thing; (S;) i. e., of a bird or flying thing, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"limb that corresponds to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yd","text_ar":"يد"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and also the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yd","text_ar":"يد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"sometimes also meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see a signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaHa","text_ar":"جَنَحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)] of a man: (L, TA:) and (K) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper arm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arm from the shoulder to the elbow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, L, K:) each of these is so called because it is on one side of the body: (L:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"armpit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajoniHapN","text_ar":"اَجْنِحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajonuHN","text_ar":"اَجْنُحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IJ, K:) the sing., though masc., has the latter pl., which properly belongs to a fem. sing. [of this form], because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jnAH","text_ar":"جناح"},{"kind":"text","text":"is assimilated to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riy$apN","text_ar":"رِيشَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IJ;) [or rather, I think, to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yadN","text_ar":"يَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is fem.;] but some assert"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jnAH","text_ar":"جناح"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be both masc. and fem. (MF.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa maqoSuwSu AljanaAHi","text_ar":"هُوَ مَقْصُوصُ الجَنَاحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has the wing clipped;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is one who lacks strength"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"power"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ability; he is impotent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xafaDa lahu janaAHahu","text_ar":"خَفَضَ لَهُ جَنَاحَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He abased himself to him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he lowered to him his wing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but see an explanation of a similar phrase in the Kur, below]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakibuwA janaAHaYi AlT~aAy^iri","text_ar":"رَكِبُوا جَنَاحَىِ الطَّايِرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, L, K,) in [some of the copies of] the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~ariyqi","text_ar":"الطَّرِيقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They quitted their homes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accustomed places."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, L, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN fiY janaAHaYo TaAy^irK","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ فِى جَنَاحَىْ طَايِرٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is in a state of disquiet, and confounded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perplexed, unable to see his right course."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, A. *) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiba fulaAnN janaAHaYi Aln~aEaAmapi","text_ar":"رَكِبَ فُلَانٌ جَنَاحَىِ النَّعَامَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one employed himself vigorously, labouriously, sedulously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diligently, in an affair;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"managing well."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naHonu EalaY janaAHi","text_ar":"نَحْنُ عَلَى جَنَاحِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~afari","text_ar":"السَّفَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We are on the wing of travel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"we are about to travel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"journey."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaAHu Alfarasi","text_ar":"جَنَاحُ الفَرَسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain star"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"γ","text_ar":"γ","orth_type":"plain"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Pegasus; one of the four bright stars, in Pegasus, which form a square;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the other three being that at the extremity of the neck, called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eayonu Alfarasi","text_ar":"عَيْنُ الفَرَسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Pegasus,] that called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manokibu Alfarasi","text_ar":"مَنْكِبُ الفَرَسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"β","text_ar":"β","orth_type":"plain"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Pegasus,] and the star ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Andromeda] that belongs to both Pegasus and Andromeda. (Kzw.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaAHu samakapK","text_ar":"جَنَاحُ سَمَكَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fin of a fish."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaAHaA","text_ar":"جَنَاحَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSolK","text_ar":"نَصْلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two wings,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blades, of a spear-head"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of an arrow-head."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaAHu Alr~aHaY","text_ar":"جَنَاحُ الرَّحَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wing"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAEuwr","text_ar":"نَاعُور"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the mill"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mill-stone."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaAHaA EasokarK","text_ar":"جَنَاحَا عَسْكَرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two wings of an army."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaAHaA AlwaAdiY","text_ar":"جَنَاحَا الوَادِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two sides of the valley"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"down which the water runs, on the right and left."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"variydapN lahaA janaAHaAni","text_ar":"ثَرِيدَةٌ لَهَا جَنَاحَانِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino EuraAqK","text_ar":"مِنْ عُرَاقٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlEuraAqi","text_ar":"بِالعُرَاقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mujan~aHapN","text_ar":"مُجَنَّحَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mess of crumbled bread moistened with broth, having two sidegarnishes of bones with some meat remaining upon them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jinoHN","text_ar":"جِنْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b3-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnibN","text_ar":"جَانِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) So in the saying in the Kur [xvii. 25],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@xofiDo lahumaA","text_ar":"وَا@خْفِضْ لَهُمَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaAHa Al*~ul~i","text_ar":"جَنَاحَ الذُّلِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA^alino lahumaA jaAnibaka Al*~aliyla","text_ar":"وَاَلِنْ لَهُمَا جَانِبَكَ الذَّلِيلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And make soft to them"},{"kind":"text","text":"[thy two parents)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy submissive side;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"treat them with gentleness and submissiveness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the former words may be literally rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lower to them the wing of submissiveness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be submissive to them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Jel, TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"junaAHN","text_ar":"جُنَاحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","Msb","L","TA","Zj","IJ","Fr","A"]},{"entry_id":"n6452","headword_ar":"جُنَاحٌ","root":"jnH","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sin, a crime,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an act of disobedience:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth, S, A, IAth, L, Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an inclining thereto:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, * L, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anxiety, and annoyance"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"molestation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hurt, which one is made to bear."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA junaAHa Ealayokumo","text_ar":"لَا جُنَاحَ عَلَيْكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur ii. 235, means, accord. to AHeyth,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There shall be no sin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crime, chargeable upon you:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to others,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"there shall be no straitening of you."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaAHN","text_ar":"جَنَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last signification."}],"source_refs":["AHeyth","S","A","IAth","L","Msb","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}